and your life in general, what
would you say is the most

00:36:05.060 --> 00:36:08.130
meaningful accomplishment
that you've had?

00:36:08.130 --> 00:36:09.470
DAVID BECKHAM: My family.

00:36:09.470 --> 00:36:10.505
My family is--

00:36:10.505 --> 00:36:12.858
[AUDIENCE APPLAUSE]

00:36:12.858 --> 00:36:14.108
DAVID BECKHAM: Aw.

00:36:16.140 --> 00:36:17.470
It really is.

00:36:17.470 --> 00:36:20.490
Obviously, I've done a lot in
my career and I've been able

00:36:20.490 --> 00:36:25.190
to be successful in different
countries and different teams

00:36:25.190 --> 00:36:26.795
and different leagues.

00:36:26.795 --> 00:36:30.040
And I'm very proud of that,
but my proudest

00:36:30.040 --> 00:36:34.500
possession is my family.

00:36:34.500 --> 00:36:36.090
MARVIN CHOW: Why don't we
take one on this side?

00:36:36.090 --> 00:36:37.830
AUDIENCE: Hi David.

00:36:37.830 --> 00:36:40.100
I wonder if you could talk a bit
about the London Olympics.

00:36:40.100 --> 00:36:43.190
Obviously, you were involved
in the bid at the time.

00:36:43.190 --> 00:36:45.800
So are you hoping for a place
in Team GB and what would it

00:36:45.800 --> 00:36:48.650
mean to you to play
at the Olympics?

00:36:48.650 --> 00:36:51.350
DAVID BECKHAM: I mean, it's
exciting for our country to

00:36:51.350 --> 00:36:54.050
host one of the biggest sporting
events in the world.

00:36:54.050 --> 00:36:56.110
I think it's really exciting.

00:36:56.110 --> 00:36:58.730
I think the buzz around England
and around London,

00:36:58.730 --> 00:37:02.565
especially around East London,
where obviously, I was brought

00:37:02.565 --> 00:37:05.580
up, it's exciting.

00:37:05.580 --> 00:37:09.420
So yes, I would love to
be part of Team GB.

00:37:09.420 --> 00:37:14.030
I've never been involved in an
Olympics, and when the team

00:37:14.030 --> 00:37:17.560
came to me and said, we want you
to be involved in the bid

00:37:17.560 --> 00:37:20.520
to get the Olympics to
our country, into

00:37:20.520 --> 00:37:23.280
London, I wasn't skeptical.

00:37:23.280 --> 00:37:27.990
But I was kind of nervous
because I'm not an athlete

00:37:27.990 --> 00:37:29.680
that has performed
in the Olympics.

00:37:29.680 --> 00:37:34.050
So I was worried what I was
going to bring to the table,

00:37:34.050 --> 00:37:37.950
and what I was going to do to
help bring it to our country.

00:37:37.950 --> 00:37:43.580
But to be there and to be part
of a successful bid to bring

00:37:43.580 --> 00:37:46.700
it to London, I was
very proud.

00:37:46.700 --> 00:37:50.650
It's one of the proudest
moments that I've been

00:37:50.650 --> 00:37:51.520
involved in.

00:37:51.520 --> 00:37:55.110
Especially, to be sat there one
side and then, the Paris

00:37:55.110 --> 00:37:57.730
side was sat at the other
side, and all the media,

00:37:57.730 --> 00:38:01.970
actually, had moved to in
front of the Paris team.

00:38:01.970 --> 00:38:04.440
So we all of a sudden got
worried, and then we expected

00:38:04.440 --> 00:38:05.510
Paris to be called out.

00:38:05.510 --> 00:38:10.300
And then London came out, and
it was an exciting time.

00:38:10.300 --> 00:38:13.280
It's going to be an
amazing game.

00:38:13.280 --> 00:38:16.412
We're going to make it proud.

00:38:16.412 --> 00:38:17.680
MARVIN CHOW: That's great.

00:38:17.680 --> 00:38:20.730
We have a question from Anushe
Ganda from London.

00:38:20.730 --> 00:38:22.640
And going back to the
proudest moment--

00:38:22.640 --> 00:38:25.310
in your footballing career
so far, what would be the

00:38:25.310 --> 00:38:27.510
proudest moment?

00:38:27.510 --> 00:38:30.220
DAVID BECKHAM: Proudest moment
in my footballing career?

00:38:30.220 --> 00:38:32.500
It would have to be
winning The Treble

00:38:32.500 --> 00:38:33.480
for Manchester United.

00:38:33.480 --> 00:38:37.510
The year '99 was a great year.

00:38:37.510 --> 00:38:41.550
I got married, I had my first
son, and we won The Treble.

00:38:41.550 --> 00:38:43.700
So it was a big year.

00:38:43.700 --> 00:38:47.596
[AUDIENCE APPLAUSE]

00:38:47.596 --> 00:38:49.830
MARVIN CHOW: We'll take a
question on this side.

00:38:49.830 --> 00:38:50.750
AUDIENCE: Hi David.

00:38:50.750 --> 00:38:53.540
Since moving to California,
what's the funniest

00:38:53.540 --> 00:38:56.080
misunderstanding you or Victoria
have had because of

00:38:56.080 --> 00:38:57.330
your accent?

00:39:01.320 --> 00:39:04.790
DAVID BECKHAM: I'm not sure
we've had a funnier one then

00:39:04.790 --> 00:39:08.860
as our children had
the other day.

00:39:08.860 --> 00:39:10.560
We were sat there
in the kitchen.

00:39:10.560 --> 00:39:16.470
Well, in our first year, and
Brooklyn was writing on a

00:39:16.470 --> 00:39:19.790
piece of paper or drawing or
doing some sketching, and he

00:39:19.790 --> 00:39:23.105
said, Daddy, I need
some rubbers.

00:39:26.760 --> 00:39:29.850
And I started looking around and
I looked over and we had a

00:39:29.850 --> 00:39:33.230
couple of friends there
from the U.S. and

00:39:33.230 --> 00:39:36.310
they looked in shock.

00:39:36.310 --> 00:39:41.110
And I didn't understand it at
the time but he now calls them

00:39:41.110 --> 00:39:41.940
erasers, anyway.

00:39:41.940 --> 00:39:43.190
[AUDIENCE LAUGHTER
AND APPLAUSE]

00:39:47.523 --> 00:39:48.230
MARVIN CHOW: That is awesome.

00:39:48.230 --> 00:39:51.440
We'll take one on this side.

00:39:51.440 --> 00:39:52.070
AUDIENCE: Hi David.

00:39:52.070 --> 00:39:53.140
Thank you for coming.

00:39:53.140 --> 00:39:54.170
Actually I don't
have an accent.

00:39:54.170 --> 00:39:56.830
I just really like yours.

00:39:56.830 --> 00:39:58.857
DAVID BECKHAM: That's
a great accents.

00:39:58.857 --> 00:39:59.731
AUDIENCE: Thanks.

00:39:59.731 --> 00:40:01.560
Yeah, so thanks for coming.

00:40:01.560 --> 00:40:05.180
I'm wondering, after today's
hangout, do you have plans on

00:40:05.180 --> 00:40:07.880
how you'd like to use hangouts
in the future, in terms of

00:40:07.880 --> 00:40:11.590
engaging with your fans
all over the world?

00:40:11.590 --> 00:40:13.200
DAVID BECKHAM: Well, I'm
hoping it goes well.

00:40:13.200 --> 00:40:16.060
Then, there will definitely
be more.

00:40:16.060 --> 00:40:20.220
I think-- this is the first
time I've done it, so it's

00:40:20.220 --> 00:40:24.240
exciting to be able to hang
out with fans that have

00:40:24.240 --> 00:40:27.280
supported me over the years
and throughout my career.

00:40:27.280 --> 00:40:30.820
It's special, and obviously it
gives them a chance to ask me

00:40:30.820 --> 00:40:34.390
questions that they've,
obviously, never been able to.

00:40:34.390 --> 00:40:37.390
So I'm excited and hopefully
there'll be more.

00:40:37.390 --> 00:40:39.370
AUDIENCE: Can I get a quick
picture with you?

00:40:39.370 --> 00:40:42.500
DAVID BECKHAM: Of
course, you can.

00:40:42.500 --> 00:40:43.912
MARVIN CHOW: Oh, it's
starting again.

00:40:48.532 --> 00:40:50.070
AUDIENCE: You look handsome
by the way.

00:40:50.070 --> 00:40:50.595
DAVID BECKHAM: Thank you.

00:40:50.595 --> 00:40:52.930
You look very lovely.

00:40:52.930 --> 00:40:53.640
MARVIN CHOW: All right, ready?

00:40:53.640 --> 00:40:56.740
1, 2, 3, cheese.

00:40:56.740 --> 00:40:57.405
There you go.

00:40:57.405 --> 00:40:58.232
AUDIENCE: Thank you.

00:40:58.232 --> 00:40:58.724
DAVID BECKHAM: No problem.

00:40:58.724 --> 00:40:59.708
Nice to meet you.

00:40:59.708 --> 00:41:00.692
MARVIN CHOW: Thank
you for coming.

00:41:00.692 --> 00:41:01.942
Thank you David.

00:41:05.120 --> 00:41:06.370
Back to the questions.

00:41:09.200 --> 00:41:12.150
Darminder Singh from the San
Francisco office asks about,

00:41:12.150 --> 00:41:14.920
throughout your career you
played against many teams.

00:41:14.920 --> 00:41:17.850
Which particular team
or set of players

00:41:17.850 --> 00:41:18.830
has left you in awe?

00:41:18.830 --> 00:41:21.120
I think you talked about
players, but maybe you could

00:41:21.120 --> 00:41:23.537
talk a little bit more on the
team side that you've played

00:41:23.537 --> 00:41:24.240
against.

00:41:24.240 --> 00:41:25.950
DAVID BECKHAM: I think teams
that I've played against that

00:41:25.950 --> 00:41:27.895
have left me in awe--

00:41:27.895 --> 00:41:29.950
I'd have to say the
Barcelona team.

00:41:29.950 --> 00:41:32.830
Every time you come up against
the Barcelona team, they play

00:41:32.830 --> 00:41:35.366
the game in such a great way.

00:41:35.366 --> 00:41:41.380
But I think the one team that
I played against that were

00:41:41.380 --> 00:41:46.500
amazing, it was where Ronaldo,
the Brazilian player, got a

00:41:46.500 --> 00:41:50.310
standing ovation from the
Manchester United fans.

00:41:50.310 --> 00:41:54.860
And that team, watching that
team, the way they played, for

00:41:54.860 --> 00:42:02.170
me- it left you kind of in awe
of the players, of the setup,

00:42:02.170 --> 00:42:05.710
of them as a club, and the
players that played there.

00:42:05.710 --> 00:42:10.690
They had Zidane, Raul, Roberto,
Carlos, Ronaldo.

00:42:10.690 --> 00:42:12.460
Little did I know I'd
be playing with

00:42:12.460 --> 00:42:13.440
them the season after.

00:42:13.440 --> 00:42:15.950
So that was exciting.

00:42:15.950 --> 00:42:19.095
But they're definitely the
team I was in awe of.

00:42:19.095 --> 00:42:19.370
MARVIN CHOW: That's great.

00:42:19.370 --> 00:42:19.780
That's great.

00:42:19.780 --> 00:42:21.780
Why don't we take a question
on this side.

00:42:21.780 --> 00:42:23.710
AUDIENCE: Your wife's been
known to wear some pretty

00:42:23.710 --> 00:42:25.100
ridiculously tall shoes.

00:42:25.100 --> 00:42:26.560
I was wondering what
your opinion is

00:42:26.560 --> 00:42:29.550
