00:44:36.050 --> 00:44:41.050
DAVID BECKHAM: I mean, my next
birthday in May I'll be 37.

00:44:41.050 --> 00:44:42.020
AUDIENCE: Still really young.

00:44:42.020 --> 00:44:42.660
It's really young.

00:44:42.660 --> 00:44:45.796
DAVID BECKHAM: In soccer years
it's not so young.

00:44:45.796 --> 00:44:47.660
AUDIENCE: But in Beckham years
it's really young.

00:44:47.660 --> 00:44:49.590
DAVID BECKHAM: In
life it's young.

00:44:49.590 --> 00:44:50.280
And I still feel young.

00:44:50.280 --> 00:44:54.940
So I'll continue to play the
game as long as can.

00:44:54.940 --> 00:44:56.350
I love it.

00:44:56.350 --> 00:44:59.730
Every single day I enjoy
going to training.

00:44:59.730 --> 00:45:01.610
I enjoy playing in games.

00:45:01.610 --> 00:45:04.730
I enjoy being part of a team.

00:45:04.730 --> 00:45:07.790
And my contract's now for two
years, so it will take me up

00:45:07.790 --> 00:45:14.710
to almost 39, almost.
And then, we'll see.

00:45:14.710 --> 00:45:20.670
I think people expected me to
move away from the Galaxy or

00:45:20.670 --> 00:45:22.970
retire at the end
of this year.

00:45:22.970 --> 00:45:27.900
So I'm excited about these
next couple of years, but

00:45:27.900 --> 00:45:30.210
we'll see what happens
in the future.

